
<div class="m-homeVertScroller">
	<h2 class="title text-center">Integration Highlights</h2>
	<ul class="timeline">
	<li class="year">1954</li>
		<li class="event">
			<h3 class="heading">Brown v. Board of Education</h3>
			<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp; May 17, 1954</span>
			
			<p>&nbsp;</p>
			<p>U.S. Supreme Court delivers its decision in Brown v. Board of Education of Topeka, Kansas, eliminating the “separate but equal” policy in American public schools.</p>
		</li>
			
			<li class="year">1961</li>
		<li class="event">
			<h3 class="heading">First African-American athlete at WVU</h3>
			<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp; 1961 </span>
			<p>&nbsp;</p>
			<p>Phillip Edwards was the first African-American athlete at WVU, participating in men's track</p>
		</li>
	<li class="year">1962</li>
		<li class="event">
			<h3 class="heading">First African-American to play football at WVU</h3>
			<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp; 1962 </span>
			<p>&nbsp;</p>
			<p>Dick Leftridge becomes the first first African-American to play football at WVU.</p>
		</li>

		<li class="event">
			<h3 class="heading">First African-American players to receive football scholarships at WVU</h3>
			<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp; 1962 </span>
			<p>&nbsp;</p>
			<p>Dick Leftridge and Roger Alford become the first African-American players to receive football scholarships at WVU.</p>
		</li>

		<li class="year">1965</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">First African-Americans On freshman basketball team</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp; 1965 </span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p>Jim Lewis, Ron Williams, Ed Harvard, and Norman Holmes make WVU sports history as the first four African-American players listed on the freshman basketball team.</p>
			</li>

			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading"> first African American athlete to play men’s soccer at WVU.</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp; 1965</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p>George Woods, Jr. became the first African American athlete to play men’s soccer at WVU.</p>
			</li>

			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">First African American athlete to wrestle at WVU</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp; 1965 </span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p>Norman Hill was the first African American athlete to wrestle at WVU</p>
			</li>
		<li class="year">1971</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">Blocking weapon for O. J. Simpson.</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp;1971</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p>Jim Braxton was the blocking weapon for star running back O. J. Simpson. As Simpson remarks, most of his 11,236 career rushing yards were due to Braxton.</p>
			</li>

		<li class="year">1972</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">Title IX Passed</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp;June 23, 1972</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p> Title IX of the U.S. Education Amendments is passed, prohibiting discrimination based on sex in educational institutions.</p>
			</li>

		<li class="year">1976</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">WVU’s first African-American baseball player</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp;1976</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p>Bruce Clinton was offered a scholarship to become WVU’s first African-American baseball player.</p>
			</li>

		<li class="year">1977</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">first African-American athlete to participate in men’s tennis</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp;June 23, 1977</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p>Harry Moore was the first African-American athlete to participate in men’s tennis at WVU.</p>
			</li>

		<li class="year">1981</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">Women's tennis</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp;1981</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p>Shirley Robinson became the first African-American female athlete at WVU, participating in women’s tennis.</p>
			</li>

		<li class="year">1984</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">Women's Basketball</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp;December 21, 1984</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p> Georgeann Wells became the first woman to register a dunk in an official NCAA intercollegiate basketball game. She did it with a men’s regulation-size.</p>
			</li>

		<li class="year">1987</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">Gymnastics</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp;1987</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p> Yvette Clark was the first African-American athlete to participate in women’s gymnastics at WVU.</p>
			</li>

		<li class="year">1993</li>
			<li class="event">
				<h3 class="heading">Gymnastics</h3>
				<span class="month"><i class="fa fa-calendar"></i> &nbsp;2006</span>
				<p>&nbsp;</p>
				<p>Marlon LeBlanc is hired as the head coach of men’s soccer at WVU, becoming the first African-American to be the head coach of a WVU sports team.</p>
			</li>

	</ul>
</div>